OL,3,CTrafford Council on 'brink of
OL,4,Cbankruptcy' amid 7.49% tax rises
OL,6,FTrafford Council's controlling Labour
OL,7,Fgroup has been accused of driving the
OL,8,Ftown hall 'to the brink of bankruptcy'
OL,9,Fat a meeting where a 7.49% council tax
OL,10,Fincreased was imposed on householders.
OL,12,FThe group were accused by Conservative
OL,13,Fopposition leader Councillor Nathan
OL,14,FEvans at a council meeting on 3 March
OL,15,Fwhich set the authority's revenue
OL,16,Fbudget for 2025/26.
OL,18,FTrafford was given dispensation by the
OL,19,FGovernment to raise its council tax
OL,20,Fabove the 4.99% threshold without a
OL,21,Flocal referendum.
