OL,4,Cbankruptcy' amid 7.49% tax rises
OL,6,FThis was part of a move by Labour to
OL,7,Fseek 'exceptional financial support'
OL,8,Ffrom the Government to try to bridge a
OL,9,Fbudget gap which jumped from #9.8m to
OL,10,F#12.8m since October.
OL,12,FThe council was also allowed to borrow
OL,13,F#9.6m from the Ministry of Housing,
OL,14,FCommunities and Local Government.
OL,16,FRepaying that loan could cost the
OL,17,Fauthority nearly #1m a year in
OL,18,Finterest payments for the next 20
OL,19,Fyears.
